g.aria-label: Yield of algae cultivation, in terms of protein per hectare per year, compared to common staple crops. Algae yields are reported byWalsh et al., with protein density of algae given by Lavens andSorgeloos. As Walsh et al. estimate yields under idealized conditions, we compare algae yields to highest yield values reported byClark and Tilmanfor wheat, maize, soybeans, and rice.Lavens, P., Sorgeloos, P. "Manual on the Production and Use of Live Food for Aquaculture". Food and AgricultureOrganization of the United Nations, Section 2.4.1996.Clark, M., Tilman, D. "Comparative analysis of environmental impacts of agricultural production systems, agriculturalinput efficiency, and food choice". Environmental Research Letters12(6).June 2017.Walsh, B. et al. "New feed sources key to ambitious climate targets". Carbon Balance and Management.December 2015.Tons protein per year per hectare
